messages.content:
Step-by-step reasoning:
1. The user wants an automation triggered by a physical on command (COC) on the device "LR1-FRONT FOYER_SW".
2. The physical on command is "Fast On" [DFON] as per the device's send commands.
3. When this command is received, set the ramp rate of "LR1-FRONT FOYER_SW" to 1.0 minute. The enum value for 1.0 minute is [12].
4. Also turn on the "KDR2-CAN LTS_SW" device to 75% brightness (On Level = 75%) and set its ramp rate to 2.0 seconds (enum value [10]).
5. Use the commands and parameters exactly as defined in the device structure.
6. No nested ifs; one top-level object with name, condition, and actions.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Front Foyer Physical On Triggers KDR2-CAN LTS_SW",
    "condition": {
      "==": {
        "device": "LR1-FRONT FOYER_SW",
        "coc": "DFON"
      }
    },
    "actions": [
      {
        "device": "LR1-FRONT FOYER_SW",
        "command": "Ramp Rate",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "Ramp Rate", "value": 12, "uom": "enum", "precision": 0 }
        ]
      },
      {
        "device": "KDR2-CAN LTS_SW",
        "command": "On",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "On Level", "value": 75, "uom": "percent", "precision": 1 }
        ]
      },
      {
        "device": "KDR2-CAN LTS_SW",
        "command": "Ramp Rate",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "Ramp Rate", "value": 10, "uom": "enum", "precision": 0 }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
